OL,4,CCovid: Catch-up tuition not helping
OL,5,Cpoorest pupils, says NAO
OL,6, The government's programme to help
OL,7, pupils who have missed school time
OL,8, catch up may not be reaching the most
OL,9, disadvantaged children, a report says.
OL,11,FThe National Tutoring Programme was
OL,12,Flaunched last year to give extra
OL,13,Ftuition to the UK's poorest pupils.
OL,15,FBut fewer than half of pupils who have
OL,16,Falready received tuition as part of the
OL,17,Fscheme are from the poorest families, a
OL,18,FNational Audit Office report found.
OL,20,FThe Department for Education says it
OL,21,Fhas invested #2bn to help pupils.
